During a press briefing, White House spokesperson Raj Shah discussed the release of the 2018 Economic Report to the President by the White House Council of Economic Advisers. The report covers the President's economic successes and future agenda. Shah also mentioned that the President is considering various proposals for gun control, such as strengthening background checks, raising the age for some gun sales, and ending the sale of bump stocks. He stated that the President is in the listening phase and will propose more concrete ideas in the future. Shah also mentioned that the President is open to providing political cover for lawmakers who support gun control measures, even if they go against the National Rifle Association (NRA). Additionally, Shah addressed questions about the President's proposal to arm teachers, stating that the focus is on having trained individuals in schools with concealed weapons to deter potential attackers. He also discussed the President's opposition to sanctuary cities and his concerns about the situation in Syria.